# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ProxmoxDeploy — Environment Configuration
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Generate this file with: ./setup.sh
#
# ── What goes where ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   .env (this file)           → DB name/user + ports (no secrets!)
#   secrets/encryption_key.txt → Vault master key (Docker Secret)
#   secrets/db_password.txt    → PostgreSQL password (Docker Secret)
#   Vault (DB, AES-256-GCM)   → Everything else (Proxmox, SSH, EntraID, etc.)
#
# On first boot, secrets from .env are auto-migrated to the vault.
# After migration they can be removed from this file.
# Manage vault entries in the web UI under Settings > Vault.
#
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── PostgreSQL (password is a Docker Secret) ────────────────────────────────
DB_NAME=proxmoxdeploy
DB_USER=proxmoxdeploy

# ── Ports ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HTTP_PORT=80
HTTPS_PORT=443

# ── Docker Secrets (required) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Generate both secret files:
#   mkdir -p secrets
#   openssl rand -hex 32 > secrets/encryption_key.txt
#   openssl rand -hex 24 > secrets/db_password.txt
#
# They are mounted at /run/secrets/ inside the containers.
# NEVER put passwords or keys in .env.
